  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA208-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu celavuṟṟāratu kuṟippaṟintu āṟṟāḷāya talaimakaḷ uraippat tōḻi colliyatu. (ET: celavuk kuṟippaṟintu āṟṟāḷāya talaimakaṭkut tōḻi coṟṟatu.)</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is what the confidante said when SHE spoke who was unable to bear it after having understood the intention of the one who was about to go.</p>
      </div>
      <div xml:id="NA208">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            viṟalcāy viḷaṅkiḻai nekiḻa vimmi</l>
<l>            yaṟalpō ṟeṇmaṇi yiṭaimulai naṉaippa</l>
<l>            viḷivila kaliḻuṅ kaṇṇoṭu peritaḻin</l>
<l>            tevaṉiṉaipu vāṭuti cuṭarnutaṟ kuṟumakaḷ</l>
<l>            celvā rallarnaṅ kātalar celiṉu </l>
<l>            nōṉmā rallar nōyē maṟṟavar</l>
<l>            koṉṉu nampuṅ kuraiyar tāmē</l>
<l>            ciṟanta vaṉpiṉar cāyalu muriyar</l>
<l>            pirinta nammiṉu miraṅki yarumporuṇ</l>
<l>            muṭiyā tāyiṉum varuva rataṉṟalai </l>
<l>            yiṉṟuṇaip pirintōr nāṭit</l>
<l>            taruvatu pōlum perumaḻaik kuralē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l rend="indent2">Sobbing, while the shining jewels become loose, [your] bravery exhausted,</l>
<l rend="indent2">greatly desolate, with eyes that weep unceasingly,</l>
<l rend="indent">so that [your] breasts become wet in between with sapphires clear as water,</l>
<l>thinking what do you fade away, little woman with glowing forehead?</l>
<l>He is not one to go, our lover, [and] even if he goes</l>
<l>he is not one to suffer such pain.</l>
<l rend="indent4">He himself</l>
<l>is one who rejoices(?), trusting greatly(?)<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">koṉ</term>, the one proclithic particle here in one of its four traditional senses: <term xml:lang="ta">perumai</term>. Disconcerting.</note> in you(?)<note place="foot">Why should we have the 2nd pl. here? This is not at all usual for the address, as is also clear from the singular of line 4.</note>.</l>
<l rend="indent2">As one of superior love and one bound to be exhausted (from lovesickness),</l>
<l rend="indent2">being grieved even more than we when separated,</l>
<l rend="indent">he will come, even if the rare wealth is not accomplished.</l>
<l rend="indent4">Moreover,</l>
<l>the voice of the great rain, it seems, will bring [him],</l>
<l rend="indent3">searching for those who are separated from [their] dear mates.</l>
        </lg>
      </div>
